fields.name: bist_start
fields.description: Writing a 1 will command the BIST FSM to sequence all steps of the BIST sequence automatically if bist_mode is 1. Otherwise it will step to the next state of the state machine if bist_mode is 0. If there is an error the BIST will restart the sequence if bist_start is written to again

fields.name: bist_mode
fields.description: 1: Sequential Mode, 0: Single Step Mode

fields.name: Rsvd1
fields.description: Reserved

fields.name: bist_done
fields.description: Each bit in this register represent on step of the BIST sequence. When the sequence starts, its reset. As each BIST step completes, its bit is set to 1

fields.name: bist_err
fields.description: Each bit in this register represent on step of the BIST sequence. When the sequence starts, its reset. As each BIST step completes, its bit is set to 1 if the sequence has completed in error

fields.name: Rsvd1
fields.description: Reserved

fields.name: err
fields.description: Indicates that an error has occured inside the FSC.
